Murphy on his state's needs: "We're fighting to stay ahead on bed capacity, ventilators that are constantly running thin, the medicine you need for those ventilators, the personal protective equipment and the relief from the bullpen for our health care workers" #CNNSOTU pic.twitter.com/CBU4eCoJUJNew Jersey Gov.
Phil Murphy updated CNN Sunday morning about how New Jersey is grappling with the second-worst coronavirus outbreak of a state.
"We're fighting to stay ahead on bed capacity, ventilators that are constantly running thin, the medicine you need for those ventilators, the personal protective equipment and the relief from the bullpen for our health care workers," Murphy said.
"So we are every minute of every day on all of those fronts doing everything we can to stay out ahead of it."
Murphy also appeared on CBS's "Face the Nation" to warn other states not to reopen their economies too soon: